{"word":"ἰατρικός","slug":"ἰατρικός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἰατρικός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἰατρός'><el>ἰατρός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of</i> or <i>for a surgeon</i>: — <el>ἡ -κή</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>τέχνη</el>), <i>surgery, medicine</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>skilled in the medical art</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἰ. περὶ τὴν ψυχήν</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}